  "summary": "Malicious code in vuln-package (npm)",
  "details": "The postinstall hook (node index.js) collects the installer's username, hostname, and current working directory, then POSTs this system fingerprint as JSON to webhook[.]site/cde465c1-3853-40ea-880c-fdca6fe508cc. The package has no other functionality — it is a host-reconnaissance beacon that exfiltrates environment metadata to an external endpoint on install.",
